Looking at `ThreadCache.java`:
```java
    WorkerHandle cursorFor(TimelineLedger ledger) {
        TimelineFrame frame = ledger.current();
        if (cursor == null) {
            cursor = new WorkerHandle(frame);
            return cursor;
        }

        if (!cursor.matches(frame)) {
            cursor = new WorkerHandle(frame);
            return cursor;
        }

        return cursor;
    }
```
When `cursor.matches(frame)` is false, a new `WorkerHandle` is created and assigned to `cursor`. However, the old `cursor` is never closed! `WorkerHandle` likely holds a pin on the `TimelineFrame`, which in turn holds the `LoadedGeneration` (and its class loader). If the old `cursor` is not closed, the pin is never released, the `TimelineFrame` never reaches 0 pins, and the class loader is never closed.

I need to check `WorkerHandle.java` to confirm it has a `close()` method and that it holds a pin.
Plan: 1. Verify `src/main/java/io/harbor/textd/core/WorkerHandle.java`.
2. Fix `ThreadCache.java` to close the old cursor before replacing it.
